          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gamma-ray detector was a multiple-detector",
                "pair-spectrometer consisting of a 7.6 cm NaI(Tl)",
                "'central' crystal (14.7 cm from target) surrounded by",
                "eight 4.2 cm diameter x 16.5 cm NaI(Tl) 'side' crystals",
                "to detect annihilation radiation.",
                "The triple-coincidence requirement reduced neutron-",
                "induced background from 2H(d,n)3He as well as cosmic",
                "ray background. A 5 cm thick Pb shield was placed",
                "around the detector assembly, and a 2.5 cm thick, 48",
                "cm x 48 cm plastic scintillator was placed on top of",
                "the assembly, yielding a total cosmic-ray suppression",
                "of about 300 for E(gamma) =20-40 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
